    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3440306450" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3440306450" />
    <a title="Fiona" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5460316-fiona"><img alt="Fiona" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1487216044p2/5460316.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3440306450?book_show_action=true">Jul 13, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Fiona" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Fiona" href="/user/show/5460316-fiona">Fiona</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5460316-fiona?shelf=crime-and-punishment">crime-and-punishment</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5460316-fiona?shelf=absolute-favourites">absolute-favourites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5460316-fiona?shelf=serial-killers">serial-killers</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3440306450" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6544868996240138878">Bone Music is just what the doctor ordered after a reading slump was threatening to develop - this book isn&apos;t perfect, but it&apos;s really good, entertaining, and (most importantly) I couldn&apos;t stop reading until I finished.<br/><br/>Charley Rowe, kidnap and trauma survivor, was an incredibly appealing protagonist. She&apos;s smart, believable, and not afraid to be direct without ever turning into the kind of blunt that usually describes itself as &quot;not afraid to speak my mind&quot; (um, no, you&apos;re probably just rude). A</span>
  <span id="freeText6544868996240138878" style="display:none">Bone Music is just what the doctor ordered after a reading slump was threatening to develop - this book isn't perfect, but it's really good, entertaining, and (most importantly) I couldn't stop reading until I finished.<br /><br />Charley Rowe, kidnap and trauma survivor, was an incredibly appealing protagonist. She's smart, believable, and not afraid to be direct without ever turning into the kind of blunt that usually describes itself as "not afraid to speak my mind" (um, no, you're probably just rude). Actually, the characters all round are the main strength of this novel; everyone is human, even the bad guys, and no-one acts in a vacuum or without motivation of <i>some</i> sort. It made for some interesting thinking; I can actually see the point of some of the arguments, but that was conflicting with the fact that these actions were also doing exactly what they claimed to want to prevent.<br /><br />There's definitely some suspension of disbelief required, because most of this takes part in a world similar to our own. It's nothing too outlandish, but the science does only pop in briefly, hand wave a few things, and then firmly distances itself from the rest of the book. But more important was the tone of the book - victims are treated with respect, people actually talk through issues both old and new, and enough shades of grey to actually paint a very realistic picture. I'm really looking forward to more from this series, which reminds me - no cliffhanger either!<br /><br /><i>Save the world? Maybe not. Make it a better place? I think so.</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="6544868996240138878" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


